  "text": "In addition, the variability of regimens was restricted compared to HIV' cohorts in Western studies. Only seven different antiretrovirals were reported, with 103 HIV' participants reporting use of non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitors (NNRTIs; efavirenz, nevirapine) and 97 reporting use of dideoxynucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitors (dNRTIs; stavudine and didanosine). Only four individuals reported use of a protease inhibitor (atazanavir [3] , nelfinavir [1]). The most common regimen was stavudine-didanosine-nevirapine, reported by 69 HIV' participants. Lastly, only 16% of treated individuals were on the most neuroeffective regimen (CPE ]2; see [CITATION_1] , for additional details on this cut-off) precluding further analysis.",
